1
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:25,166
♪ I THINK IT'S TIME
WE BLOW THIS SCENE ♪

2
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:27,583
♪ GET EVERYBODY
AND THEIR STUFF TOGETHER ♪

3
00:00:27,666 --> 00:00:31,208
♪ OK, 3, 2, 1,
LET'S JAM ♪

4
00:01:46,958 --> 00:01:49,541
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

5
00:01:50,166 --> 00:01:52,791
[BUBBLING]

6
00:02:31,125 --> 00:02:32,083
AAH!

7
00:02:32,166 --> 00:02:36,125
[PANTING]

8
00:02:36,208 --> 00:02:38,791
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

9
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:04,875
HMM.

10
00:03:04,958 --> 00:03:06,291
[DOG WHINES AND BARKS]

11
00:03:06,375 --> 00:03:08,250
[PANTING]

12
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:10,416
[CHUCKLES]

13
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:15,166
[DOG WHINING]

14
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:17,958
UM!

15
00:03:18,041 --> 00:03:18,958
[PANTING]

16
00:03:19,041 --> 00:03:20,458
IF YOU DON'T WORK,
YOU DON'T EAT.

17
00:03:20,541 --> 00:03:21,916
YOU'RE A HUNTING DOG.

18
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,125
HUNT UP SOME FOOD.

19
00:03:24,791 --> 00:03:26,250
WE GIRLS ARE DIFFERENT.

20
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:30,166
WE HAVE TO BE PAMPERED BECAUSE
WE'RE DELICATE AND REFINED.

21
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:33,208
[SLURPING]

22
00:03:33,291 --> 00:03:35,083
MMMMM.

23
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,500
HMM.

24
00:03:39,583 --> 00:03:41,583
3 MILLION WOOLONG REWARD?

25
00:03:41,666 --> 00:03:45,583
WELL, I'LL JUST HAVE
THE BOYS GET IT FOR ME, THEN.

26
00:03:46,916 --> 00:03:47,916
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

27
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,500
DAMN, THAT BLUES
HARP SOUNDS SWEET.

28
00:03:50,583 --> 00:03:51,416
I KNEW IT WOULD.

29
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:54,125
HMM! I THOUGHT
YOU LIKED JAZZ.

30
00:03:54,208 --> 00:03:55,625
DON'T BE DENSE.

31
00:03:55,708 --> 00:03:56,833
I STARTED WAILING THE BLUES

32
00:03:56,916 --> 00:03:58,708
WHEN THE DOCTOR
WHACKED MY BOTTOM

33
00:03:58,791 --> 00:04:00,208
ON THE DAY I WAS BORN.

34
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:02,833
A BABY HIPSTER... VERY COOL.

35
00:04:02,916 --> 00:04:05,166
[BEEPING]

36
00:04:05,250 --> 00:04:08,625
NO DOUBT ABOUT IT,
IT'S GIRAFFE.

37
00:04:08,708 --> 00:04:09,458
ALL RIGHT.

38
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:11,125
I'M GOING IN FROM THE RIGHT.

39
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:12,500
YOU TAKE THE LEFT SIDE.

40
00:04:12,583 --> 00:04:14,708
LARD BOY IS IN THE WAY.

41
00:04:14,791 --> 00:04:17,666
HMM? OH!

42
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:18,916
THAT'S FATTY.

43
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
MAKE A MOVE, JET.
THE BALL'S IN YOUR COURT.

44
00:04:21,083 --> 00:04:23,666
HMM.

45
00:04:23,750 --> 00:04:25,166
YO! HEY, FATTY!

46
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:26,583
--HUH?
--FATTY RIVER!

47
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:29,625
--LONG TIME NO SEE, BUDDY!
--OH! WHO'D HAVE GUESSED?

48
00:04:29,708 --> 00:04:30,958
IF IT ISN'T JET BLACK.

49
00:04:31,041 --> 00:04:34,250
WELL, WELL. WHEN THE HELL
DID YOU BLOW IN?

50
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:35,125
HOW ABOUT YOU?

51
00:04:35,208 --> 00:04:36,375
YOU'RE LOOKING PRETTY CHEERY.

52
00:04:36,458 --> 00:04:38,625
WHAT HAPPENED?
DID YOU CATCH A NICE BIG ONE?

53
00:04:38,708 --> 00:04:40,750
[BOTH LAUGHING]

54
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:44,458
I HAD NO IDEA YOU WERE
A FAN OF THE BLUES, FATTY.

55
00:04:44,541 --> 00:04:45,666
YOU KIDDING ME?

56
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:46,708
I LISTENED TO THE BLUES

57
00:04:46,791 --> 00:04:48,625
WHEN I WAS STILL
IN MY FATHER'S SACK,

58
00:04:48,708 --> 00:04:50,041
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

59
00:04:50,125 --> 00:04:52,125
[BOTH LAUGHING]

60
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:15,250
[NO AUDIO]

61
00:05:23,625 --> 00:05:25,625
UNH!
UH, SORRY.

62
00:05:25,708 --> 00:05:27,625
HEY!

63
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:38,375
[DING]

64
00:05:43,625 --> 00:05:45,333
[TONE SOUNDS]

65
00:05:56,375 --> 00:05:57,875
HMPH!

66
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:08,791
GIVE IT BACK NOW!

67
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:11,625
ZEBRA!

68
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:14,666
YAAH!

69
00:06:17,291 --> 00:06:18,666
[GASPS]

70
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:49,708
HEY, YOU! WAKE UP!

71
00:06:49,791 --> 00:06:51,250
HEY!

72
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:52,166
AW, GREAT.

73
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:53,916
YOU DIE, AND I LOSE THE REWARD.

74
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,958
DON'T... DON'T
BE FOOLED BY HIM...

75
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:58,291
BY THE WAY HE LOOKS.

76
00:06:58,375 --> 00:07:00,833
DON'T TALK!
TRY TO STAY ALIVE!

77
00:07:00,916 --> 00:07:02,750
NOT ME.

78
00:07:02,833 --> 00:07:05,000
HE NEEDS HELP NOW.

79
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:06,916
HELP HIM.

80
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:11,333
THIS STONE...

81
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:16,375
[SIRENS WAILING]

82
00:07:16,458 --> 00:07:17,791
WAIT!

83
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:20,666
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

84
00:07:34,916 --> 00:07:36,541
[BEEP]

85
00:07:39,791 --> 00:07:41,416
[BEEPING]

86
00:07:43,125 --> 00:07:44,208
HMM.

87
00:07:44,291 --> 00:07:45,916
I CAN'T BE SURE
UNTIL I RUN ALL THE TESTS,

88
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,958
BUT THIS MAY BE WORTH
A HEFTY SUM.

89
00:07:49,041 --> 00:07:50,791
SO WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO DO WITH IT?

90
00:07:50,875 --> 00:07:52,125
I HAVE NO IDEA.

91
00:07:52,208 --> 00:07:53,791
THE GUY GIVES IT
TO ME ON HIS OWN,

92
00:07:53,875 --> 00:07:55,125
THEN HE DIES ON HIS OWN.

93
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:57,458
I DON'T SEE ANY REASON
WHY WE SHOULDN'T KEEP IT.

94
00:07:57,541 --> 00:07:59,000
THERE IS NO REASON.

95
00:07:59,083 --> 00:08:02,000
YOU'RE NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR THAT KID, AFTER ALL.

96
00:08:02,083 --> 00:08:03,166
GIVE ME THAT!
HMM.

97
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:05,875
THIS THING IS GOING
TO PAY FOR OUR FOOD.

98
00:08:05,958 --> 00:08:07,500
OUR FOOD, NOT YOURS.

99
00:08:07,583 --> 00:08:09,958
YOU KNOW, I THINK YOUR
HEART'S MADE OUT OF LEAD.

100
00:08:10,041 --> 00:08:12,875
NOT LIKE ME.
I'M A NICE GUY.

101
00:08:12,958 --> 00:08:13,916
I HAVE A GIFT FOR YOU.

102
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:17,041
YAY!
ALL RIGHT, WHAT IS IT?

103
00:08:18,166 --> 00:08:19,958
AN OFFICIAL INVOICE?

104
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:21,250
AN INVOICE FOR WHAT?

105
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:23,125
ALL THE EXPENSES
YOU'VE RACKED UP

106
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:24,791
SINCE YOU'VE BEEN ON OUR SHIP.

107
00:08:24,875 --> 00:08:26,375
AND THANKS FOR YOUR BUSINESS.

108
00:08:26,458 --> 00:08:29,541
YEAH. GREAT. ANYTIME.

109
00:08:29,875 --> 00:08:33,500
WHY DO YOU WANT
TO KNOW ABOUT THIS DEAD GUY?

110
00:08:33,583 --> 00:08:34,541
WELL, UH...

111
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:38,750
HA! SO YOU WERE
AFTER GIRAFFE, TOO.

112
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:41,583
DID YOU GET A GOOD DEAL?

113
00:08:41,666 --> 00:08:42,541
HMM?

114
00:08:42,625 --> 00:08:45,125
[CHUCKLES]
ENJOYING THE SWEETS?

115
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:46,125
I ALWAYS DO.

116
00:08:46,208 --> 00:08:48,208
THERE'S NO BOUNTY IN IT,
YOU KNOW.

117
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:49,291
YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

118
00:08:49,375 --> 00:08:51,000
THERE'S NOTHING TO
GAIN HERE AT ALL.

119
00:08:51,083 --> 00:08:52,666
HMM.
NO, I MEAN IT.

120
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:54,208
THERE'S NOTHING
ON THE LINE HERE.

121
00:08:54,291 --> 00:08:55,500
YEAH, RIGHT, JET.

122
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:57,791
YOU'RE GOING TO OWE
ME ONE FOR TODAY.

123
00:08:57,875 --> 00:08:59,041
ALL RIGHT.
YOU KNOW THAT KID

124
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:01,125
ON THE BLUES HARP
THE OTHER DAY? NAME'S WEN.

125
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:05,166
GIRAFFE WAS AFTER
THE KID'S SO-CALLED FATHER,

126
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,958
AN OLD FRIEND.
HE GOES BY THE NAME ZEBRA.

127
00:09:07,041 --> 00:09:07,958
THEY WERE FRIENDS?

128
00:09:08,041 --> 00:09:09,833
SHEESH!
YOU DIDN'T EVEN KNOW THAT?

129
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,000
THE TWO OF THEM WERE THE LEADERS

130
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:12,791
OF THE SELF-DEFENSE
VOLUNTEER SQUAD.

131
00:09:12,875 --> 00:09:16,041
THEY WORKED TOGETHER
UNTIL ABOUT 10 YEARS AGO.

132
00:09:16,125 --> 00:09:18,833
I DON'T GET IT.

133
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:21,000
WHY WAS HE AFTER AN OLD COMRADE?

134
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:23,791
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

135
00:09:23,875 --> 00:09:25,833
10 YEARS AGO,
THEY HAD A CONFRONTATION

136
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:29,958
WITH SOME SPACE RAIDERS
A LAND DISPUTE.

137
00:09:30,041 --> 00:09:34,333
IT ALL CAME DOWN AT SOME
R&amp;D FACILITY NEAR MARS.

138
00:09:34,416 --> 00:09:38,541
A FEW DAYS LATER,
THE RAIDERS ARE WIPED OUT,

139
00:09:38,625 --> 00:09:39,791
ZEBRA IS MISSING,

140
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:43,541
AND GIRAFFE IS FOUND
BLINDFOLDED IN A SILO.

141
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:46,083
THEY SAY ZEBRA
DOUBLE-CROSSED HIM

142
00:09:46,166 --> 00:09:47,875
SO HE COULD RUN THE SQUAD SOLO.

143
00:09:47,958 --> 00:09:52,583
LATER, ZEBRA TURNS UP
IN A WHEELCHAIR WITH THE KID.

144
00:09:52,666 --> 00:09:56,833
GUESS IT DIDN'T TURN OUT
THE WAY HE PLANNED.

145
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:59,500
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

146
00:10:01,458 --> 00:10:02,750
SO THE BOTTOM LINE IS,

147
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:05,958
GIRAFFE WAS KILLED OFF
OVER SOME INTERNAL POLITICS.

148
00:10:06,041 --> 00:10:08,208
BETRAYAL MAY COME
EASILY TO WOMEN,

149
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:10,791
BUT MEN LIVE BY
IRON CODES OF HONOR.

150
00:10:10,875 --> 00:10:11,875
YOU BELIEVE THAT?

151
00:10:11,958 --> 00:10:15,000
I'M TRYING TO, REAL HARD.

152
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:17,916
[HARMONICA PLAYING]

153
00:10:26,583 --> 00:10:28,125
[HARMONICA STOPS]

154
00:10:43,375 --> 00:10:45,958
TELL ME... WHO ARE YOU?

155
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:49,000
JUST SOME SUSPICIOUS GUY.

156
00:10:49,083 --> 00:10:50,458
WHAT DO YOU WANT HERE?

157
00:10:50,541 --> 00:10:52,833
BEFORE GIRAFFE
BOUGHT THE FARM,

158
00:10:52,916 --> 00:10:55,750
HE ASKED ME TO COME
HERE TO HELP YOU.

159
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:01,416
BUT ZEBRA SHOT GIRAFFE.

160
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,333
UHHUH.

161
00:11:03,416 --> 00:11:06,125
THEN WHY WOULD GIRAFFE
ASK HIM TO HELP THE KID?

162
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:07,666
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

163
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:10,333
HMM? HEY, THE KID'S
IN THE HEADLINES.

164
00:11:10,416 --> 00:11:13,041
GUESS HE MUST BE
PRETTY FAMOUS, HUH?

165
00:11:13,125 --> 00:11:14,125
YEAH.

166
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:17,375
KID'S A GENIUS.
PLAYS LIKE AN OLD PRO.

167
00:11:17,458 --> 00:11:19,125
HMM?
[GASPS]

168
00:11:19,208 --> 00:11:19,958
HEY, WAIT A MINUTE!

169
00:11:20,041 --> 00:11:21,666
THIS GUY ISN'T ZEBRA.

170
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:22,791
WHAT'S THAT?

171
00:11:22,875 --> 00:11:25,666
LOOK CLOSE.
CAN'T YOU SEE THE DATE?

172
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:26,708
WHAT THE HELL?!

173
00:11:26,791 --> 00:11:29,083
THIS WAS PUBLISHED 30 YEARS AGO.

174
00:11:29,166 --> 00:11:32,125
HOW CAN HE HAVE THE SAME FACE?

175
00:11:32,208 --> 00:11:33,000
COME ON.

176
00:11:33,083 --> 00:11:35,166
THERE'S NOTHING TO BE AFRAID OF.

177
00:11:35,250 --> 00:11:36,875
COME HERE. LET'S TALK.

178
00:11:36,958 --> 00:11:38,708
[GUNSHOT]
UNH!

179
00:11:39,291 --> 00:11:41,625
YOU'D BETTER STAY OUT OF IT.

180
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:43,000
HUH?

181
00:11:43,083 --> 00:11:45,250
LITTLE TWERP LIKE YOU
STICKS HIS NECK OUT TOO FAR,

182
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:48,333
HE'LL GET IT CUT OFF.
UNDERSTAND?

183
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:51,041
AAH!

184
00:11:51,125 --> 00:11:52,500
DON'T GIVE ME THAT CRAP, KID!

185
00:11:52,583 --> 00:11:54,416
SORRY, BUT I'M NOT A KID.

186
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:56,458
YEAH.
ALL KIDS SAY THAT.

187
00:11:56,541 --> 00:11:59,583
I KNOW WHAT I LOOK LIKE,

188
00:11:59,666 --> 00:12:02,708
BUT I WAS ALIVE
WHEN THIS PLACE WAS AN OUTPOST,

189
00:12:02,791 --> 00:12:05,375
BEFORE THE ASTEROIDS
WERE EVEN SETTLED.

190
00:12:05,458 --> 00:12:07,750
GET THE PICTURE?

191
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:30,166
[BLUES HARMONICA PLAYING]

192
00:13:03,791 --> 00:13:06,166
[RUMBLING]

193
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,375
[THUNDER]

194
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:56,250
THE HYPERSPACE GATE
HAD BLOWN TO BITS.

195
00:13:56,916 --> 00:14:01,708
FROM THAT DAY ON, MY BODY
COMPLETELY STOPPED AGING.

196
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:03,250
I CAN'T DIE.

197
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:05,875
THERE WAS ALWAYS
SOMEONE DISCOVERING ME,

198
00:14:05,958 --> 00:14:07,041
DOING EXPERIMENTS,

199
00:14:07,125 --> 00:14:09,583
BUT THEY ALL DIED,
AND I KEPT ON LIVING.

200
00:14:09,666 --> 00:14:11,000
THE END FOR THIS GUY STARTED

201
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:14,416
WHEN HIS SELF-DEFENSE
VOLUNTEER SQUAD HIT OUR R&amp;D LAB.

202
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,500
I NEEDED A NEW COVER,

203
00:14:15,583 --> 00:14:17,666
SOMEONE TO PLAY
THE PART OF MY PARENT.

204
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:21,333
DON'T... DON'T
BE FOOLED BY HIM...

205
00:14:21,416 --> 00:14:23,916
BY THE WAY HE LOOKS.

206
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,708
NOT ME.

207
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:28,458
HE NEEDS HELP NOW.

208
00:14:28,541 --> 00:14:30,833
HELP HIM.

209
00:14:33,291 --> 00:14:36,791
I THINK HE'S THE THIRD GUY
I'VE USED LIKE THIS.

210
00:14:36,875 --> 00:14:39,458
NOW, WHERE'S THE RING?

211
00:14:39,541 --> 00:14:40,416
RING?

212
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:41,750
WHAT RING?

213
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:42,708
[GUNSHOT]
UNH!

214
00:14:42,791 --> 00:14:44,958
THAT'S OK.
EVEN IF YOU HAD IT,

215
00:14:45,041 --> 00:14:48,958
IT'D JUST BE A CASE OF
CASTING PEARLS BEFORE SWINE.

216
00:14:49,041 --> 00:14:50,791
[COCKS GUN]
UNH!

217
00:14:50,875 --> 00:14:53,250
[GUNFIRE]

218
00:15:01,583 --> 00:15:02,666
[RELOADS GUN]

219
00:15:02,750 --> 00:15:05,125
[GUNFIRE]

220
00:15:13,958 --> 00:15:14,833
[GUNSHOT]
UNH!

221
00:15:14,916 --> 00:15:17,041
[GUN CLATTERS TO FLOOR]

222
00:15:18,708 --> 00:15:20,333
[GUNSHOT]

223
00:15:28,541 --> 00:15:29,833
UNH!

224
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,375
[GUNFIRE]

225
00:15:35,125 --> 00:15:36,708
AAH!

226
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:39,541
[CRASH]

227
00:16:00,916 --> 00:16:04,041
AW, QUIT COMPLAINING,
YOU BIG KLUTZ.

228
00:16:04,125 --> 00:16:07,708
YOU'RE LUCKY YOU GOT AWAY WITH
THIS LITTLE SCRATCH ON YOUR ARM.

229
00:16:07,791 --> 00:16:11,000
BUT WE DON'T HAVE THE MONEY
TO PAY FOR A FUNERAL.

230
00:16:11,083 --> 00:16:12,833
I'M SORRY.

231
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:14,375
HMM?

232
00:16:14,458 --> 00:16:16,333
HMM.

233
00:16:16,666 --> 00:16:18,458
[DOG BARKING]

234
00:16:18,541 --> 00:16:19,541
CAN IT, EIN!

235
00:16:19,625 --> 00:16:21,500
DON'T BE OBNOXIOUS.

236
00:16:21,583 --> 00:16:23,458
[DOG WHINING]

237
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:27,166
HUH?

238
00:16:32,250 --> 00:16:34,375
HMM?

239
00:16:34,458 --> 00:16:38,041
JET... THE ALPHACATCH.

240
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:45,083
[BEEPING]

241
00:16:45,166 --> 00:16:46,500
AW, CRAP.

242
00:16:46,583 --> 00:16:48,041
THIS PIECE OF JUNK!

243
00:16:48,125 --> 00:16:49,458
ALL RIGHT.

244
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:53,458
NOW... WHAT DO YOU
MAKE OUT OF THIS?

245
00:16:56,625 --> 00:16:58,458
A HOTEL ROOM. THAT'S IT.

246
00:16:58,541 --> 00:17:01,416
HE'S REMEMBERING THE TIME
GIRAFFE GOT BLOWN AWAY.

247
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,083
GIVE IT BACK NOW!

248
00:17:03,166 --> 00:17:05,958
ZEBRA, COME OVER HERE! HURRY!

249
00:17:06,041 --> 00:17:06,833
DAMN.

250
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:08,625
AND THEN WHAT?

251
00:17:08,708 --> 00:17:11,541
COME ON, WHAT DID GIRAFFE SAY?

252
00:17:13,583 --> 00:17:14,625
I HAVE IT NOW.

253
00:17:14,708 --> 00:17:16,333
I CAN DO YOU IN WITH THIS.

254
00:17:16,416 --> 00:17:20,666
THIS STONE HAS THE POWER
TO RETURN TIME TO YOU.

255
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:24,958
NOW, HAND ZEBRA OVER TO ME!

256
00:17:25,375 --> 00:17:27,083
ZEBRA!

257
00:17:27,166 --> 00:17:28,541
[GUNSHOT]

258
00:17:28,625 --> 00:17:31,583
[BLUES HARMONICA PLAYING]

259
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:57,500
WHEN THE GATE EXPLODED,
A COORDINATE SYSTEM WAS CREATED

260
00:17:57,583 --> 00:17:59,541
FROM THE RESULTING
TWISTS IN HYPERSPACE

261
00:17:59,625 --> 00:18:03,208
A KIND OF SINGULARITY THAT
DREW IN VAST AMOUNTS OF ENERGY,

262
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:07,541
ENCLOSING AND CRYSTALLIZING
THEM INTO A SINGLE-FACETED STONE

263
00:18:07,625 --> 00:18:10,541
THE GEM THAT MAKES UP THIS RING.

264
00:18:11,625 --> 00:18:14,333
THE SAME ENERGY BROKE
WEN'S CIRCADIAN RHYTHM.

265
00:18:14,416 --> 00:18:16,458
HIS PINEAL BODY
CONTINUALLY PRODUCES

266
00:18:16,541 --> 00:18:18,833
A SUBSTANCE LIKE MELATONIN

267
00:18:18,916 --> 00:18:20,500
THAT INHIBITS AGING.

268
00:18:20,583 --> 00:18:23,458
THAT'S THE THEORY IN A NUTSHELL.

269
00:18:23,541 --> 00:18:24,875
GET THE PICTURE?

270
00:18:24,958 --> 00:18:26,250
YEAH, AS IF.

271
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,666
HMM.
I DON'T, EITHER,

272
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:31,291
WHICH SIMPLY MEANS...
THERE'S NO WAY TO KNOW FOR SURE

273
00:18:31,375 --> 00:18:35,583
UNTIL WE STICK THE GEM
INTO THE KID AND FIND OUT.

274
00:18:38,583 --> 00:18:40,166
ANYTHING COULD HAPPEN.

275
00:18:40,250 --> 00:18:43,166
IT COULD BLOW SKYHIGH
THE MOMENT IT HITS.

276
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:46,708
KIND OF MAKES IT INTERESTING.

277
00:18:55,416 --> 00:18:56,375
YES, MY DEAR?

278
00:18:56,458 --> 00:18:57,750
I JUST THOUGHT
I'D SAY GOODBYE, SPIKE,

279
00:18:57,833 --> 00:19:00,458
SINCE I'M SURE IT'S THE LAST
TIME I'LL BE SEEING YOU.

280
00:19:00,541 --> 00:19:02,625
HUH! YOU MEAN,
YOU'RE FINALLY LEAVING US?

281
00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:06,208
NO! I MEAN YOU'RE
NOT COMING BACK.

282
00:19:08,666 --> 00:19:10,416
[FLICKS LIGHTER]

283
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:12,416
[CLICK]

284
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:16,250
I DON'T LIKE THIS SETUP, JET.

285
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:18,958
DON'T LIKE IT AT ALL.

286
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:30,166
MEN ARE SUCH TOTAL IDIOTS.

287
00:19:41,875 --> 00:19:44,458
[GUNSHOT]
[WINDOW SHATTERS]

288
00:19:44,541 --> 00:19:48,291
[DOG BARKING]

289
00:20:06,708 --> 00:20:11,458
[GUNFIRE]
[TIRES SQUEALING]

290
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:41,750
[GUNSHOTS]

291
00:20:54,708 --> 00:20:56,375
[GUNSHOT]

292
00:20:59,916 --> 00:21:01,708
[GASPS]

293
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:07,666
[GASPS]

294
00:21:36,458 --> 00:21:40,625
[GASPING AND MOANING]

295
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:52,666
UH, UH...

296
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:53,750
I SEE.

297
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:56,875
YES, I CAN FINALLY DIE AT LAST.

298
00:21:56,958 --> 00:22:00,333
UH, I FEEL SO HEAVY...

299
00:22:00,416 --> 00:22:06,833
UH... BUT I FEEL
I FINALLY FEEL AT EASE.

300
00:22:06,916 --> 00:22:09,583
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

301
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:16,083
DO YOU UNDERSTAND? DO YOU?

302
00:22:24,208 --> 00:22:27,791
[BLOWS INTO HARMONICA]

303
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:33,083
YEAH, I UNDERSTAND.

304
00:22:33,166 --> 00:22:35,166
AS IF.

305
00:22:45,166 --> 00:22:47,125
BANG.

306
00:24:26,958 --> 00:24:28,041
[MAN SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY]

307
00:24:28,125 --> 00:24:31,916
[SPEECH INAUDIBLE
OVER LOUD ROCK MUSIC]

308
00:24:32,416 --> 00:24:34,458
YOU KNOW WHAT
HEAVY METAL IS, RIGHT?

309
00:24:34,541 --> 00:24:36,583
WHAT DID YOU SAY?
HEAVY METAL!

310
00:24:36,666 --> 00:24:37,750
I SAID, HEAVY METAL!

311
00:24:37,833 --> 00:24:39,083
WHAT?!
I CAN'T HEAR YOU!

312
00:24:39,166 --> 00:24:41,500
HEY! CAN YOU DO SOMETHING
ABOUT ALL THAT NOISE?

313
00:24:41,583 --> 00:24:43,916
IT'S GOING TO BE RUNNING
THROUGH THE WHOLE NEXT EPISODE.

314
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,875
I THINK I'LL STAY
OUT OF IT, THEN!

315
00:24:45,958 --> 00:24:47,916
I CAN'T HEAR A WORD
YOU'RE SAYING!

316
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,875
NEXT EPISODE
HEAVY METAL QUEEN!

317
00:24:49,958 --> 00:24:52,333
IS THIS REALLY
GETTING THROUGH TO ANYONE?

